B.YU=new A.cY("CREW STATS","Each crew member has three personal stats:\n\nLOYALTY \u2014 how much they trust your command. If the crew average drops below 15, they mutiny and the run ends.\n\nFEAR \u2014 how scared they are. High fear makes crew erratic and amplifies tension.\n\nHOPE \u2014 belief that the mission matters. Low hope drags loyalty down over time.")
B.YZ=new A.cY("CIVILIAN TENSION","A ship-wide pressure gauge (0\u2013100). Civilian crew members push this up when you make harsh or authoritarian choices. At 70 you will see warning signs. At 90 the situation is critical. At 100 the civilians seize the ship \u2014 run over.")
B.Z3=new A.cY("YOUR BACKGROUND","The background you choose at the start shapes your crew's starting loyalty and your credit reserve:\n\nVANGUARD CONSCRIPT \u2014 career soldier. Citizens respect you immediately. Starts with a modest credit bonus.\n\nCIVIC OFFICER \u2014 administrator turned commander. Diplomatic credibility, largest starting credit reserve.\n\nMEDTECH SPECIALIST \u2014 field medic. Crew trusts you with their lives. Small credit bonus, high crew goodwill.")
B.YT=new A.cY("CREW ENCOUNTERS","Some encounters let specific crew members act. Their loyalty, fear, and background influence outcomes. A low-loyalty crew member sent on a dangerous task may not follow through. A terrified civilian may refuse orders under pressure.")
